Venari repository rules

- Keep shared addon behavior in src/Venari/*.lua only when it is genuinely
  portable across supported clients.
- Put client/version-specific implementation details in the matching
  ports/<version>/VenariPort.lua file.
- Shared code may call VenariPort APIs, but it must not inline TBC, MoP,
  locale/build-number, spell ID, or client API compatibility branches.
- When adding support for a new client behavior, add or extend a port API
  first, then keep src/Venari/*.lua as version-neutral callers.
